Shell Scitping:

    ~~Special Variables:

    The filename of the current script (script name) - $0

    The number of arguments supplied to a script - $#

    All the arguments/variables are individually double quoted to passed to script - $@

    The exit status of the last command executed - $? (if 0-success othenthan 0 (1-127) -failure)

    The process ID of the current shell script - $$

    The process number of the last background command - $!

    present working directory - $PWD

    home directory of the user who is running the script: $HOME

    which user is running the script: $USER

Colors:

    Red="\e[31m"
    Green="\e[32m"
    Yellow="\e[33m"
    No color="\e[0m"